      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Badly damaged, partially reconstructed ossuary. Lid is missing. Ornamentation, on the chest's front side, consists of two metopes in a doubled zigzag frame and a broadened triglyph flanked by zigzags. Triglyph contains an upright branch with alternating carved and smooth leaves, each with superimposed tendrils in freehand. Each metope contains a twelve-petalled rosette within a zigzag circle. Badly damaged inscription is on the chest's right side. שמעון is a very common name.</p>
         </div>
